{"title":"Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 2: Mons-en-Pévèle","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-mons-en-pevele","date":1744200797000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-mons-en-pevele\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 2: Mons-en-Pévèle</a></p>\n\n<p>‘If you get through here, you’ve really made it to the “final” of Paris-Roubaix,’ says <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/mat-hayman-2016-paris-roubaix\">Mat Hayman</a>, ‘although there is still a way to go.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Australian labels the 3km section of cobbles at Mons-en-Pévèle, which comes just 50km from the finish in <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-velodrome\">Vélodrome André-Pétrieux</a>, as key to his own victory here in 2016. It was also key in his failure to defend his title in 2017.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘Often it’s where the race really gets broken up, which means it’s nice to get off Mons-en-Pévèle and be at the front, as you know you’re really in the mix then.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So much so that Hayman points out that the first five riders off that section in 2016 – him, Tom Boonen, Ian Stannard, Sep Vanmarcke and Edvald Boasson Hagen – made up the top five at the finish in Roubaix.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2048\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mons-en-pevele-massaro.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mons-en-pevele-massaro.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mons-en-pevele-massaro-300x225.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mons-en-pevele-massaro-970x728.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mons-en-pevele-massaro-768x576.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mons-en-pevele-massaro-1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mons-en-pevele-massaro-750x563.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mons-en-pevele-massaro-1140x855.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption>Mike Massaro</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>‘It really is a very good indicator of how people are going.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While the famous <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-arenberg-forest\">Arenberg Forest</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/where-paris-roubaix-2022-will-be-decided-part-3-carrefour-de-l-arbre\">Carrefour de l’Arbre</a> sectors of pavé are never far from anyone’s lips when talking about <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-all-you-need-to-know\">Paris-Roubaix</a>, Mons-en-Pévèle, introduced into the race in 1978 and a regular feature ever since, may just be the most significant sector that doesn’t come to mind.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But you might say ‘oh yeah!’ when you’re reminded that it was here in 2016 that <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/fabian-cancellara-podcast\">Fabian Cancellara</a> was eliminated from among Hayman’s potential rivals after taking a tumble.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+7\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-7-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-7-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-7-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-7-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-7-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-7-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-7-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-7-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It was a crash that saw World Champion <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/peter-sagan-podcast\">Peter Sagan</a> all-but bunnyhop one-footed over the Swiss rider’s bouncing bike and somehow stay upright, riding on as though nothing had happened.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also where, in 2006, George Hincapie busted his handlebars (actually it was his steerer tube that snapped) and subsequently his collarbone in the resulting crash.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-paris-roubaix\">How to watch Paris-Roubaix 2025</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-carrefour-de-l-arbre\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 3: Carrefour de l’Arbre</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-velodrome\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 4: Roubaix Velodrome</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-arenberg-forest\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 1: The Arenberg Forest</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-all-you-need-to-know\">Paris-Roubaix 2025 preview: Routes, favourites, how to watch, start lists and history</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"645\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-970x645.webp\" alt=\"fabian cancellara crashes on the mons-en-pevele cobble sector at 2016 paris-roubaix\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-768x511.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-1536x1021.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-2048x1362.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-750x499.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-1140x758.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/GettyImages-529095584-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Tim De Waele via Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The incident left him sitting in the bordering field in disbelief at what had just unfolded, shedding tears of pain mixed with tears of frustration and the knowledge that it wasn’t going to be the year that he bettered his second place of 2005.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And although he’d return another five times for a crack at it – riding the event a total of 17 times during his career – second was as good as it would ever get for the American, or indeed any American.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, for Cancellara, there were happier times on Mons-en-Pévèle’s pavé in 2010 when he attacked – or ‘simply’ rode away from – sole hanger-on Björn Leukemans to solo to the finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It was the second of what would eventually be three wins at Roubaix (including twice doing the ‘Flanders-Roubaix double’ in 2010 and 2013) before his retirement at the end of the 2016 season.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Missed the first in this series? Check out <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-arenberg-forest\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided part 1: The Arenberg Forest</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-mons-en-pevele\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 2: Mons-en-Pévèle</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Martin James","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"9bd0534d4526be80e7b64ba7821f7ba64022aa0a48fbfe39e094c39a9cbd7f46","category":"Cycling"}